title: Jeff Merkley
message:
In a moment I'm going to ask you to donate a few dollars to my campaign. But first I want to tell you why this matters right now.

This past summer when I heard reports that there were children ripped from their mothers' arms and locked in cages I was horrified. I hoped it wasn't true.

So I went to the border to get the truth. You remember the video -- there I was at a former WalMart in Brownsville trying to get in to find out how the children there were being treate...d. They refused to let me in and even called the local cops on me.

These children are victims of Donald Trump's political agenda. He's deliberately harming them because he thinks it helps him politically.

It's wrong it's immoral and it's a stain on our nation.

I'm not going to give up this fight. No matter how many times the White House attacks me.

Let's show Donald Trump that you won't give up this fight either -- in the only language he understands: money. Chip in $5 right now and stand with me. Let's keep building this movement to live up to our American values of decency and dignity for everyone. And let's meet our most basic responsibility as adult human beings and protect children from harm.

I refused to listen to those who said that if gun safety legislation couldn't pass after Sandy Hook then it never could.

Now six years later the... House has finally passed universal background check legislation ‚Äì but it won‚Äôt pass the Senate unless we turn up the pressure right now. We need another 879 petition signatures before midnight to reach our goal of 650000 people demanding the Senate pass this critical bill and it looks like you haven‚Äôt signed yet. title: Elizabeth Warren
message:
We have a problem in this country: Money has too much influence on our political leaders. The amount of money you can give shouldn‚Äôt determine the amount of time you get to spend with a candidate. So I‚Äôve made a decision: My presidential primary campaign will be run on the principle of equal access for anybody who joins it. It means that wealthy donors won‚Äôt be able to purch...ase better seats or one-on-one time with me at our events. And it means I won‚Äôt be doing ‚Äúcall time‚Äù which is when candidates take hours to call wealthy donors to ask for their support.

I am grateful for every donation we get ‚Äî and we need every single one! ‚Äî but what matters more much more is that everybody who supports my campaign is treated equally regardless of how much they can afford to give. message:
Okay -- here‚Äôs the truth: I am going to ask you to make a donation to my campaign in just a few moments. It‚Äôs not my favorite thing about running for president but it‚Äôs important and I hope you will let me explain why it matters so much.

I‚Äôll start here: I am not taking a dime from corporate PACs or federal lobbyists -- and that was a very deliberate choice. It means we are intentionally leaving resources on the table. But that‚Äôs ok with me. I never want there to be any ques...tion about whether I‚Äôm listening to the people or special interests.

That‚Äôs why the average donation to fundraising messages like this one is generally about $20 -- and why I believe grassroots donors are going to sustain our movement into this primary.

Here‚Äôs the other reason: this week I am huddling with my team to evaluate the budget and our plans to build a winning campaign. The more money we raise before our mid-month fundraising deadline tonight the more we can compete -- especially in early states like Iowa South Carolina Nevada and New Hampshire.

The choices we make in this meeting will set the tone and pace for the rest of our campaign. I am running to win -- so we are pushing our team as hard as we can because there is just no other option.

title: Sandy Hook Promise
message:
My beautiful butterfly Dylan was shot at least five times in his first-grade classroom at Sandy Hook Elementary. He died in the arms of his special education assistant when he was just six years old.

Now a company called Revived Games has turned that day into a game. They have created a video game where the objective is to murder people in a school ‚Äì and even after it was removed from one gaming platform they're still planning to release it.

This is absolutely sickening. It ...disgusts me to think that someone saw what happened to my son and every person injured or killed in a school shooting and thought it would make a fun game for other people to play. They're actually trying to make money by glorifying school shootings.

I need 100000 people to join me in demanding that Revived not release or sell this game. But we're currently still very short and it looks like you haven't signed yet. So please sign the petition right now!

‚Äì Nicole Hockley (Dylan's mom)

title: Save The Bees
message:

The Save The Bees Project was created to give people around the world a place to support this cause.

If you cannot purchase a product you can still help this cause by sharing and liking this post as well as our page and we will happily give you a free product from our website in exchange for this you can find those products on our promotions page :)

If you would like to join millions of people around the world in fighting to Save The Bees click learn more.

Proceeds and audiences raised through our website are used for:

1. Raising Awareness to the General population about Bees and their importance to the enviroment through using paid ads to spread the message.

2. Using paid marketing to drive traffic to likeminded communities/causes/movements around the world who are also trying their best to make a difference.

3. Directly donating proceeds to various likeminded causes that we support. A list of causes that we currently support will be listed on our about page with a direct link to their website.

4. Using paid marketing to build an Email list so we can spread helpful petitions for bans on harmful pesticides or practices around the world that need signatures to pass.

5. Using proceeds to source or create environmentally friendly Beekeeping products or Bee produced products such as Natural Beeswax.

More information can be found on our About Page.

title: Save The Bees
message:
What does a flower resemble to you

To us humans in our every days lives flowers resemble any one of a million things.

They are given as gifts to loved ones on special occasions to resemble love happiness beautiful memories from the past and the promise of more to come in the future.

They are used as a message of hope and comfort when someone falls sick.

They are given as a thank you to a friend or family member when words don't quite suffice.

They are the perfect present to get some of us out of a sticky situation when our imperfections get the better of us and the word sorry doesn't quite cut it.

To a Bee a flower is the perfect example of unity. the interaction of two organisms which produce a combined effect greater than the sum of their separate effects.

To put it plainly Bees and Flowers are better off together than alone they are stronger healthier and would cease to exist without eachother.

To a Bee a Flower is everything. There is no bias to the type or the size or the shape. We could learn a thing or two from Bees.

To a Bee a Flower is life love and beauty all wrapped in one.

So what does a flower resemble to you

To us this flower represents our commitment to having a positive impact on Bee populations are the world.

Bee populations around the world are currently in decline and that's no good for anyone.

We as humans are responsible and it's time for us to step up and give back to our furry little friends. They've had our backs forever and now it's time for us to have theirs.

Join us in our commitment to Saving The Bees Here and tell us what this a flower resembles to you ‚û°Ô∏è https://savethebeesproject.com/products/bee-inspired
